  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>About the Role</p><p>We are looking for a <strong>Sales Coordinator</strong> to support our <strong>regional logistics operations</strong> based in Singapore. This role focuses on shipment coordination, logistics documentation, and order processing across multiple overseas markets.</p><p>The position is suitable for candidates who are <strong>detail‑oriented, systematic, and willing to work within established procedures</strong>, and who are interested in developing their skills in a structured logistics environment.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Process customer orders and invoices accurately and in a timely manner</p></li><li><p>Prepare and verify logistics documentation such as commercial invoices, packing lists, and shipping documents before submission</p></li><li><p>Coordinate shipments with appointed freight forwarders or airlines based on established shipment guidelines</p></li><li><p>Communicate with customers and internal teams on shipment instructions, order status, and documentation requirements</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal departments (sales & service, production, transport) to support order fulfilment</p></li><li><p>Ensure accuracy and completeness of documents prior to release</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate records in internal systems and spreadsheets</p></li><li><p>Support logistics operations for Singapore and assigned regional markets</p></li><li><p>Participate in regular team discussions to review issues and support continuous improvement</p></li><li><p>Assist with system‑related activities, including ERP preparation and data accuracy tasks</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma in Supply Chain, Logistics, Business Administration, or a related field (preferred)</p></li><li><p>1–3 years of relevant experience in logistics, order processing, or operations</p></li><li><p>Basic understanding of international shipment and logistics documentation</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working with spreadsheets and computerized systems (ERP exposure is an advantage)</p></li><li><p>Good communication and coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Detail‑oriented, organized, and able to follow structured workflows</p></li><li><p>Willing to clarify uncertainties early and work collaboratively with the team</p></li></ul>",
